::: {.callout-important}
## The Core Lesson
Automatic selection is no substitute for thinking. The algorithm has no understanding of your research question. A model should reflect your understanding of the phenomenon, not just patterns in a particular sample.
:::

### Cross-Validation as a Safeguard {#sec-ch7-cv}

One partial safeguard against overfitting is **cross-validation** (CV). The idea is simple: instead of evaluating a model on the same data used to build it, we repeatedly hold out a portion of the data, fit the model on the remainder, and evaluate predictions on the held-out fold. If selected predictors are genuine, the model should perform similarly on the held-out data. If they are false positives capitalizing on sample-specific noise, the model will perform noticeably worse out of sample.

**$k$-Fold Cross-Validation** partitions the data into $k$ roughly equal-sized subsets (folds). For each fold $j = 1, \ldots, k$:

1. Hold out fold $j$ as the **test set**
2. Fit the model on the remaining $k - 1$ folds (the **training set**)
3. Predict the outcome for the held-out observations and compute the prediction error (e.g., RMSE)

The final CV estimate of prediction error is the average across all $k$ folds. Common choices are $k = 5$ or $k = 10$.

::: {.panel-tabset}
### Output

::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code  code-fold="true" code-summary="Show R Code"}
data(hsb_sub)
set.seed(640)

# Define 5 folds
k <- 5
fold_ids <- sample(rep(1:k, length.out = nrow(hsb_sub)))

# Three competing models
model_formulas <- list(
  "Theory-driven (Step 4)" = mathach ~ ses * sector + minority + female,
  "Full additive"          = mathach ~ ses + female + minority + size + sector,
  "Stepwise"               = formula(step(
    lm(mathach ~ 1, data = hsb_sub),
    scope = list(
      lower = lm(mathach ~ 1, data = hsb_sub),
      upper = lm(mathach ~ ses + female + minority + size + sector, data = hsb_sub)
    ),
    direction = "both", trace = 0
  ))
)

# Run 5-fold CV for each model
cv_results <- purrr::map_dfr(names(model_formulas), function(mod_name) {
  purrr::map_dfr(1:k, function(j) {
    train <- hsb_sub[fold_ids != j, ]
    test  <- hsb_sub[fold_ids == j, ]
    fit   <- lm(model_formulas[[mod_name]], data = train)
    preds <- predict(fit, newdata = test)
    rmse  <- sqrt(mean((test$mathach - preds)^2))
    tibble(Model = mod_name, Fold = j, RMSE = rmse)
  })
})

# Summary table
cv_summary <- cv_results |>
  group_by(Model) |>
  summarise(Mean_RMSE = mean(RMSE), SD_RMSE = sd(RMSE), .groups = "drop") |>
  mutate(across(where(is.numeric), \(x) round(x, 3)))

cv_summary |>
  kable(
    col.names = c("Model", "Mean RMSE", "SD RMSE"),
    caption = "Five-fold cross-validation results for three competing models",
    align = "lcc"
  )
```

