  const testColor = pal.secondary;

  const cardStyle = (color) => `
    display: inline-flex; flex-direction: column; align-items: center;
    padding: 12px 18px; border-radius: 8px; min-width: 140px;
    background: ${overfit_withAlpha(color, 0.08)};
    border: 1.5px solid ${overfit_withAlpha(color, 0.3)};
  `;
  const labelStyle = (color) => `font-size: 12px; font-weight: 600; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.5px; margin-bottom: 4px; color: ${color};`;
  const valueStyle = (color) => `font-size: 22px; font-weight: 700; color: ${color}; font-family: monospace;`;

  const warnColor = overfit_isOverfitting ? pal.secondary : pal.success;
  const warnLabel = overfit_isOverfitting ? "Overfitting!" : "Good fit";

  return html`<div style="display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 12px; justify-content: center; margin-top: 8px; color: ${tc.text};">
    <div style="${cardStyle(trainColor)}">
      <span style="${labelStyle(trainColor)}">Training R²</span>
      <span style="${valueStyle(trainColor)}">${overfit_currentTrainR2.toFixed(3)}</span>
      <span style="font-size: 0.75rem; color: ${trainColor}; opacity:0.7;">p = ${overfit_nPredictors}</span>
    </div>
    <div style="${cardStyle(testColor)}">
      <span style="${labelStyle(testColor)}">Test R²</span>
      <span style="${valueStyle(testColor)}">${overfit_currentTestR2.toFixed(3)}</span>
      <span style="font-size: 0.75rem; color: ${testColor}; opacity:0.7;">p = ${overfit_nPredictors}</span>
    </div>
    <div style="${cardStyle(pal.info)}">
      <span style="${labelStyle(pal.info)}">Best Test R²</span>
      <span style="${valueStyle(pal.info)}">${overfit_bestTestR2.toFixed(3)}</span>
      <span style="font-size: 0.75rem; color: ${pal.info}; opacity:0.7;">at p = ${overfit_bestTestP}</span>
    </div>
    <div style="${cardStyle(warnColor)}">
      <span style="${labelStyle(warnColor)}">Status</span>
      <span style="font-size: 18px; font-weight: 700; color: ${warnColor};">${warnLabel}</span>
      <span style="font-size: 0.75rem; color: ${warnColor};">Gap = ${overfit_gap.toFixed(3)}</span>
    </div>
  </div>`;
}
```


## Model Fit Criteria {#sec-ch7-criteria}

### $R^2$ and Adjusted $R^2$

$R^2$ always increases with more predictors --- it cannot be used alone for model comparison. **Adjusted $R^2$** penalizes for complexity:

$$
R^2_{\text{adj}} = 1 - \frac{(1 - R^2)(n - 1)}{n - k - 1}
$$ {#eq-ch7-adjr2}

Adjusted $R^2$ **can decrease** when a new predictor doesn't help enough to offset the complexity penalty.

### AIC and BIC

$$
\text{AIC} = -2 \log L + 2k, \qquad \text{BIC} = -2 \log L + k \log(n)
$$ {#eq-ch7-aic-bic}

- **AIC**: Optimized for prediction; lower is better
- **BIC**: Penalizes complexity more heavily; optimized for model identification

::: {.callout-note}
## AIC vs BIC
- **AIC** is better for **prediction** — selects the model that minimizes expected prediction error
- **BIC** is better for **explanation** — identifies the "true" model as $n \to \infty$
- When AIC and BIC disagree, BIC's selection is simpler. Report both.
:::

